Pepper...and Salt
("As cold war fades, some nations' spies seek industrial
secrets." -- WSJ news item)
                                                                                                       

   The recent sharp decline in
   The degree of East-West tensions
   Has caused some foreign agents
   To apply for early pensions.
   While other spies have changed
   The definition of defector --
   Instead of foreign governments
   They join the private sector.
   -- Marshall E. Cobb.
   ---
   Roll Call
                                                                                                       

   The bagel's held in such regard,
   You don't hear many knocks on it --
   In fact, for fear a thief is near,
   A lot of us put lox on it.
   -- Dick Emmons.